Proof: Let P ′ i 1 , P ′ i 2 and P ′ i 3 be the contour paths of C ′ i . According to the definition of a corner cycle, one of them, say P ′ i 1 , is a green path on C o ( G ), but none of the child-cycles of C ′ i has a green path on C o ( G ). (In Fig. 15 all green paths of the child-cycles of C ′ i are drawn by thick lines.) Since P ′ i 1 is on C o ( G ), none of the child-cycles of C ′ i has a green path on P ′ i 1 .
